channel.title: No one can connect to my server
channel.description:
[center][b]I have port forwarded, and canyouseeme.org can see me on port 43594. I've put my no-ip into the client.java folder, and yes I compiled. I've restarted my router, I've restarted my computer, no-ip DUC is updating my host, I've tried having uTorrent on and off, but every time I try to log on it says "No response from server. Please try using a different world". [/b][/center]
[center]I'm getting very sick and tired of asking people how to fix this. I have asked and asked, but NO ONE has made an attempt at helping me.
[b]TELL ME WHAT I AM DOING WRONG. PLEASE.[/b][/center]

item.title: No one can connect to my server
item.dc:creator: @iZombz iZombz
item.description:
@iZombz wrote:

I am 100% sure. I have been viewing EVERY thread that seems similar to mine. I done EVERYTHING people have suggested in other threads. But there is NOTHING here about what my issue is. And no one is willing to go on teamviewer to see for themselves what the problem is.

I NEED to get this server up. There are people who are really counting on me to get this done. But I am just stumped.
